Incompatible property definition override

The property definition overrides a property in a parent class, but the override is not compatible.

The accessor VI in the child class and the accessor VI in the parent class must have the same access to the same private data or not be an accessor VI to any private data. If you have an accessor VI in both the parent and child classes, both VIs must be accessors for the same private data, which is defined by the long name of the property. Both the accessor VIs also must have the same read, write, or read/write access to the private data.
